Color. Coloration in life as observed in situ by MBARI ROV footage appears uniform black with a lighter band over the snout slightly anterior to the midpoint between the eye and the snout tip (
Fig. 4
). After preservation specimens are uniform dark brown or purplish, including all paired and unpaired fins, with no distinct markings or mottling. Claspers are slightly lighter in color.
